  "text": "Therefore, some additional ingredients or assumptions must be introduced into the present model in order to cope with the η-η ′ system. Since going beyond ladder approximation is not within the scope of the present work, the following scheme is the most sensible at this level: note that there is a standard way (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) to account for the anomaly effect by parametrizing it through the term λ η added to the η 0 mass, since only this singlet combination (11) is coupled to the gluon anomaly, so that only its mass is affected by it. This corrects the U A (1) problem arising in the mass matrix evaluated with the nonet SU(3) f -states η 8 and η 0 . Let us do the same in our mass matrix (47):",
